<item>
            <title>[LU-13565] LNet socklnd with NAT is not working properly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13565</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sihara&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sihara&quot;&gt;sihara&lt;/a&gt; found this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When using NAT on a setup, it appears like the wrong NID is used:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;peer 1: 192.168.122.135 (NAT: 10.128.13.120)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
(lib-move.c:1790:lnet_handle_send()) TRACE: 192.168.122.135@tcp(192.168.122.135@tcp:&amp;lt;?&amp;gt;) -&amp;gt; 10.128.13.130@tcp(10.128.13.130@tcp:10.128.13.130@tcp) : GET &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;# 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;peer2: 10.128.13.130&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
(lib-move.c:4302:lnet_parse()) TRACE: 10.128.13.130@tcp(10.128.13.130@tcp) &amp;lt;- 10.128.13.120@tcp : GET - &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; me

(lib-move.c:1858:lnet_handle_send()) TRACE: 10.128.13.130@tcp(10.128.13.130@tcp:10.128.13.130@tcp) -&amp;gt; 10.128.13.120@tcp(10.128.13.120@tcp:10.128.13.120@tcp)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;peer1:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
:(lib-move.c:4236:lnet_parse()) TRACE: 10.128.13.120@tcp(192.168.122.135@tcp) &amp;lt;- 10.128.13.130@tcp : REPLY - routed
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears like the NID is of the node changes some where along the line.&lt;br/&gt;
LNet shouldn&apos;t care about NAT in this case and should work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
